 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 4: The government is exploring the possibility of restricting the export of iron ore to save and promote domestic steel utilities in the forthcoming national mineral policy. ?If export of quality ore continues unabated, it would in the long run jeopardise the future of our own domestic steel utilities, which we cannot allow to happen,? Union steel minister Ram Vilas Paswan said.

 Mumbai, April 4: Gujarat Ambuja Cements today said the open offer made to its shareholders by Holcims subsidiary Holderind Investments Ltd for acquiring 20.28 per cent stake has been revised. The offer for acquisition of up to 27.43 crore fully paid-up equity shares of Rs 2 each at a price of Rs 90.64 per share would now open on April 5 and close on April 24

 New Delhi, April 4: IRDA has issued anti-money laundering guidelines that include strict adherence of know-your-client (KYC) norms by insurance companies. IRDA has asked the insurers to put in place a policy framework by July 1 as the regime becomes effective from August 1.

 Mumbai, April 4: IL amp;FS Investment Managers Ltd today said it would raise $60 million through issue of securities in the international markets for meeting its funding requirements. 

 New Delhi, April 4: Fieo today sought tax exemptions as well as refunds on buying raw materials from domestic markets to boost exports from the country.




